Package com.paypal.selion.configuration

A package which contains configuration information for SeLion.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Initializer
    This interface represents the capabilities that any initializer must possess so as to let SeLion automatically invoke it (even if the implementation resides downstream).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractConfigInitializer
    An abstract implementation that guarantees configurations to be initialized via ServiceLoader.
    Config
    A configuration object that contains properties needed throughout SeLion.
    ConfigManager
    This class supports configuration operations on SeLion local configurations LocalConfig being used in TestNG suites.
    ListenerInfo
    A utility class that stores some information pertaining to a Listener.
    ListenerManager
    TestNG 6.1 provides a capability wherein you can hook in Listeners via ServiceLoading.
    LocalConfig
    A local configuration object that contains SeLion configuration property values (i.e.
    LoggerConfig
    The SeLion Logger configuration and Logger related properties.
    OSSConfigInitializer
    A Simple initializer to prioritize initialization related to the Config initializations.
    SeLionBuildInfo
    A simple object which allows users to extract build time information related to SeLion.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Config.ConfigProperty
    SeLion config properties
    ExtendedConfig
    Commonly referred SeLion configurations.
    LoggerConfig.LoggerProperties
    Enum which contain the SeLion logger properties.
    SeLionBuildInfo.SeLionBuildProperty
    SeLion build time properties
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ConfigException
    This exception is supposed to be thrown in case something goes wrong while setting up the configuration values either default or user provided
